Brazil ,  Colombia  and Vietnam will
maintain their dominance of the coffee market, according to
Supremo SA, a coffee trader in Brugge, Belgium.  Over the past 21 years, these countries have increased
their market share of world production to 57 percent from 46
percent, Paul Cooke of Supremo said today at a conference in
Antwerp, Belgium.  Brazil is the worldâ€™s largest producer of the commodity,
followed by Vietnam. Colombia is the second-largest producer of
